<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, BUMPER AND RUNNING BOARDS - MXT - REMOVE AND INSTALL - HOOD SEAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HOOD SEAL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The hood seal is mounted along the cowl tray and forms a protective seal between the engine
                compartment and the cowl tray.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Seal- Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release the hood latches on each side and tilt the hood forward all the way.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grip the hood seal (Item 1, Figure 43) and lift in upward direction and remove entire
                    length of seal (Item 1, Figure 43) from cowl tray (Item 2, Figure 43).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901343" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901343.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Hood Seal Passenger Side Shown</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. COWL TRAY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Seal- Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place hood seal (Item 1, Figure 43) on the forward edge of the cowl tray (Item 2, Figure
                    43) and press down on seal causing the trim lock portion to secure on the cowl tray edge.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Continue across the entire forward edge of the cowl tray with the hood seal material.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press seal down on edge as far as is allowable. Lower hood and latch hood release.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
